                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Edward</forename> 
                           <surname>Madison</surname>, merchant of <orgName role="person" key="org_109074">the Staple, Calais</orgName>
                        </persName>,
                  and <persName nymRef="Madison">
                           <forename>Joan</forename> his wife</persName>, formerly wife
                  of <persName>
                           <forename>Morgan</forename> 
                           <surname>Williams</surname>
                        </persName>, deceased, 
                  acknowledges to have received of the abbot of <orgName role="abbot" key="org_109067">Oseney</orgName> 5 marks sterling 
                  of a certain annual rent of 20 marks, payable for the lives of the said Morgan and Joan. 
                  Dated in the <orgName role="date" key="org_109001">church of St. Thomas of Acon</orgName>, <origDate notBefore="1526-04-22" notAfter="1527-04-21">2 Nov., 18 Hen. VIII</origDate>. 
